Download jenkins, unzip the file to get jenkins.war file
From the cmd, go to the location of jenkins.war file and run "java -jar jenkins.war". 
It will make the jenkins up and running and also we can see one admin password 
We can access jenkins hitting url : 'http://localhost:8080/' in the browser
It will ask for password, we need to give the password which is shown in the cmd while running jenkins war file
It will ask us to choose the option to install plugin and ask us to create new user.
Then we can launch jenkins file.
